  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Credit Analyst (Corporate Banking)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coverage of general corporates as well as local and foreign large conglomerates.</li>\n  <li>Perform independent credit analysis and evaluation, including financial analysis and projections on new and existing banking facilities/ loans tomake recommendations for approval.</li>\n  <li>Identify key risks and mitigating factors in the credit evaluationandpresent cases to the Credit Committee for deliberation and approval.</li>\n  <li>Conduct customer visits together with Front office to understandthebusiness operations</li>\n  <li>Plan and organize to ensure credit reviews are completed in timelymanner.</li>\n  <li>Review credit documentation to ensure adherence to approved Termsand Conditions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 3 years credit experience in a major bank with exposure to various industries and loan products including trade finance.</li>\n  <li>University degree.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Interested candidates please email resume in <strong>MS Word format</strong> to <strong>recruit@waterstone.com.sg</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Please state your last drawn and expected package, relevant skill sets and the position you are applying for.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Resumes collected will be kept in strict confidence and used for recruitment purposes only.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>",
